comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/statelibraryofnsw/] This photograph is identified as Downshire Street, between Pottinger and Lower Fort Street, in the book My Town: Sydney in the 1930s by Lydia Gill (Sydney : State Library of NSW Press, 1993), p. 54. The view is south-south-east towards Ferry Lane. The Hero of Waterloo on Windmill Street can be seen in the distance. Refer to the large size of this map to place in context [http://www.flickr.com/photos/state-records-nsw/4931127422/]
